  "text": "Kajantie and coworkers [CITATION_1] presented further evidence pointing to the association between preeclampsia and cardiovascular events in the offspring. The authors followed subjects born from 6410 singleton pregnancies, attended at two maternal hospitals in Helsinki, between 1934 and [123]",
